<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-09T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-09T03:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2573: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-09T16:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            9, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received December 9, 3 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Referring to Department’s telegram of December 8 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>], 4 p.m. I informed bankers on their arrival the
                                Legation could not support loan without instructions from the
                                Department. Bankers decided to go ahead without waiting for approval
                                of the Department. The Chinese Minister of Finance informs me that
                                the five million has already been paid by Pacific Development
                                Corporation. Reorganization of Wine and Tobacco Administration is
                                understood to be proceeding according to the terms of the loan
                                agreement.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>